Hi and welcome to the first stage of our recruitment process

Itâs really important for us to know whether we are right for you and if you are right for us (it is Chemistry after all!).You probably know what we do by now (if not, you can visit our weabsite) so as you would expect we put a lot of emphasis on getting this right.

By submitting your details and responses, you consent to The Chemistry Group (trading as AHK Recruitment Limited) using your information as set out in our Privacy policy. You also consent to our End User Licence Agreement and Acceptable Use Policy. For information as to how your prospective employer may use your information, please refer to their privacy policy.
Hi and welcome to the first stage of our recruitment process
Thank you for completing the âFit for Sky Retailâ Questionnaire.
'Continue' to start the Day in the Life of a Sky SRS Advisor/Walker assessment.
I am not an emotional person.
Welcome to 'A Day in the life of an SRS Advisor'
This is designed to assess how you could deal with everyday situations as an SRS Advisor and to give you the opportunity to learn more about the role.
Throughout this assessment, you will be faced with typical situations. You will then be asked to state how you would respond to the situation.
Don't try to overthink it. Answer with your first feeling and intuition.
Go somewhere quiet to complete it.
Take as much time as you need, this assessment isn't timed! It will take you approximately 20 minutes to complete.
Click Continue to see an example situation you would be asked to rate.
Don't try to overthink it. Answer with your first feeling and intuition.
A customer approaches you and asks for more information about Sky's new products and promotions. She seems interested however tells you she can't stay long to talk.
Provide her with some information to think about, thank her and wish her a good day.
Promote and highlight the latest Sky products and promotions to create a positive impression. Focus on ensuring the customer leaves feeling good.
Ask if she is interested in buying from Sky and focus on progressing the conversation towards closing a sale.
Tell her you completely understand and apologise for interrupting her day.
When you are ready, please click Start*

*By clicking the "Start" button you agree that you have read the information above, you understand how to answer the questionnaire, and that you are agreeing to complete the 'Day in the Life of' assessment.
Your information is confidential and will only be used to inform our recruitment decisions.
It's great to see you're interested in working for Sky, we canât wait to hear more about you. To apply for a Retail role, we would like to invite you to complete two online assessments
'Fit for Sky Retail' questionnaire â This is a 10 minute questionnaire which is designed to help us understand your values and motivations.

'A Day in the Life of an SRS Advisor/Walker' â This is a 20 minute experience that will provide you with the opportunity to understand what it is like to work in the role. You will be faced with real-life situations and be asked to decide how you would respond.
We expect these two online experiences will take you approximately 30 minutes to complete. You will be provided with instructions before starting each assessment.

Promote and highlight the latest Sky products and promotions to create a positive impression. Focus on ensuring the customer leaves feeling good.

Tell her you completely understand and apologise for interrupting her day.
